      "content": "Certainly! Substantive due process ensures fairness beyond the procedural steps. It’s a constitutional doctrine that bars the state from enforcing laws that infringe on fundamental rights, even when those laws are duly enacted. For instance, in cases like Lochner v. New York, the Supreme Court invalidated a state law limiting bakers' work hours, deeming it as interfering with the freedom to contract. This exemplifies how substantive due process serves as a safeguard against unjust laws, emphasizing the essence and spirit of rights protected, rather than the mere form of legal procedures.",
